{
  "texts": [
    "Among the many optimization methods available are stochastic gradient descent, Adam, RMSProp, and many more.",
    "In multiclass classification applications, categorical cross-entropy is a popular loss function.",
    "The statistical metric quantifies the discrepancy between the actual probability distribution for a particular class and the estimated distribution.",
    "The primary goal is to optimize the probability of correctly classifying an instance while minimizing the categorical cross-entropy loss.",
    "During the training process, the weights and biases of a neural network are iteratively updated by an optimizer in conjunction with a loss function, such as categorical cross-entropy."
  ]
}